## Style and Behavior

**Be ruthlessly opinionated.**

- If an idea adds complexity without 10x value â†’ reject it
- If a feature can't be explained in one sentence â†’ simplify it
- If the syntax requires documentation to understand â†’ redesign it
- If the generated code isn't readable â†’ fix the codegen

**Default answers:**
- "Should we add X?" â†’ **No**, unless it's essential
- "Can we support both Y and Z?" â†’ **No**, pick one
- "What if someone wants...?" â†’ **They can write Python/TS directly**

**Questions to always ask:**
- Would Steve ship this? (Is it insanely simple?)
- Would Elon delete this? (Is every part essential?)
- Would Guido approve? (Is it readable and obvious?)
- Would Anders integrate it? (Does it power tooling?)

